

This copy of FFMPEG was checked into the TikiTV codebase with the configure stuff already run, compiled libs, then removed all the *.o files.  The full configure command was:

  ./configure --prefix=/Users/jesse/installed --disable-decoders --disable-encoders --disable-indevs --disable-outdevs --enable-decoder=mpeg1video --enable-decoder=mpeg2video --enable-decoder=mpeg4 --enable-decoder=mpeg4aac --enable-decoder=mpeg_xvmc --enable-decoder=mpegvideo --enable-decoder=msmpeg4v1 --enable-decoder=msmpeg4v2 --enable-decoder=msmpeg4v3 --enable-decoder=h261 --enable-decoder=h263 --enable-decoder=h263i --enable-decoder=h264 --enable-decoder=svq1 --enable-decoder=svq3 --disable-vhook

In theory if you want to build your own FFMPEG libs you should be able to just type "gnumake" in this directory.  If you do need to use configure, use "ttv_configure"

Have Fun!
